<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3727] Nested top-level class causes problems</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3727</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Groovy fails to deal correctly with starting a class involving a top-level nested class.  So:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;NestedClassProblem {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;NestedClass { }
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; void main ( &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[] args ) { }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;results in the error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caught: groovy.lang.GroovyRuntimeException: This script or class could not be run.&lt;br/&gt;
It should either: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;have a main method,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;be a JUnit test, TestNG test or extend GroovyTestCase,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;or implement the Runnable interface.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which as well as being unexpected, is not really an inferable outcome.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 9.04 Jaunty Jackalope, Groovy HEAD 2009-09-05</environment>
