                            <comment id="14467614" author="roshandawrani" created="Mon, 7 Sep 2009 21:27:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will it help if module classes are sorted at classgen phase end so that outer classes come before the inner classes?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any other suggestion that can be tried?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467689" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 8 Sep 2009 08:24:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;when the class is defined in the classloader it needs sorting, but the order there is wrong for us. Since the inner class holds a class name of the outer class the outer class needs to be loaded first, or else loading the class won&apos;t be possible. So we need first to define the outer, then the inner class. No we need a different solution for this. The class selection is in general a bit unstable... I am thinking that we maybe should save the first class and then reorder to put that at first or at last a defined position. In case of a script we have to prefere the script of course.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467870" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 12:32:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
